dialogStrings:
{Aeris}
“This guy is sick.”{PAUSE}“He passed out nearby and
someone must have helped him here.”

“That guy in the pipe's a weird one.
No matter what you ask him,
he only answers 'uuh' or 'aahh'.”

“Even with all that commotion,
you went on like nothing happened.
You must've really been through
the mill to get like that.”

“I don't know, they might even
be better off this way.”{PAUSE}“Even though they know the planet is on its
last legs, there's nothing they can
do about it.”{PAUSE}“I wish I could close myself off like that.”

“These folks went
wobbling off somewhere…”{PAUSE}“They said something about the
'Reunion starting'… sounded almost like a
chant. Wonder what the heck that meant.”

“…sniff…sniff…”{PAUSE}“First there was a rumbling…
…then cracking…
and then ker-blaMM!!…”{PAUSE}“…I was so scared…sniff…”

“Outta the way! Move!
You want something?
Move into the store!”

“You finally think you're making a
living in the pits of Midgar,
and then a big piece of scrap like
that falls down here…what's next?”

“Yeah, that's right!
But even so, where could we
move to now?”

“It's a market in the slums of Sector 6.
They've got everything you
could ever want there.”{PAUSE}“If you can get there,
that is. The road's something else.”

“Oh yeah? Then maybe I should
have you pick something up for
me next time you're there…”

“What's going on with the world?
When it's all said and done,
we're all gonna wind up dead.”

“You've been talking like that
for sometime now.”

“What am I doing? I'm walking around
looking at the ground.”{PAUSE}“You find a lot of things people
dropped when you look down.
You never find them when
you're looking up. Right?”

“Never thought that would
come tumbling down.
Maybe I better walk around
looking up from now on.”

“I'm not going to look up or down!
From now on I'm just going to
look straight ahead.”{PAUSE}“Maybe not.
I'm just flapping my gums.
I really wonder how things
will turn out.”
